  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7, then peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong>, then chop your <strong>coriander</strong>, including the stalks (save some leaves for a garnish!)</p><p>Peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely chop (or grate) <strong>half</strong> your <strong>ginger</strong>, then slice the<strong> remaining ginger</strong></p><p>Wash your<strong> pak choi</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper and chop into quarters lengthways</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-copy-7-1678455828181-x200.jpg",
