          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-copy-3-1678455841217-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped pak choi </strong>to a large piece of <strong>tin foil</strong> (or two!) with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> and the<strong> sliced ginger</strong></p><p>Scrunch the foil around the pak choi to form a tightly sealed parcel and add to a baking tray</p><p>Tip: Cooking for 3 or more? Make 2 separate parcels!</p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 15-20 min or until the pak choi is tender – this is your <strong>ginger pak choi</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-copy-3-1678455845940-x200.jpg",
