    {
      "instruction": "<p>Drain your <strong>king prawns</strong> and pat them dry with<strong> </strong>kitchen paper, then set aside 3 <strong>drained prawns</strong> per person and<strong> </strong>chop the <strong>remaining prawns</strong> until they are finely minced</p><p>Combine your <strong>pork mince </strong>(remove the paper if required!) and the <strong>minced</strong> <strong>prawns </strong>in a large bowl with the <strong>grated garlic</strong>, <strong>chopped coriander</strong>,<strong> grated ginger</strong>,<strong> panko breadcrumbs</strong>, <strong>red Thai curry paste </strong>and a pinch of<strong> salt</strong>, then divide and shape into 3 <strong>patties </strong>per person, then press a <strong>reserved prawn </strong>firmly<strong> </strong>into the top of each patty – these are your <strong>Thai-style patties</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-copy-4-1678455850223-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
